==>Create Project: File -> New -> Project-> Select maven -> click next
==>Name: mycucumberproject: finish->click on EnableAutoImport(IF YOU SEE)
==>Add Dependencies : Selenium-java, webdrivermanager,cucumber java, cucumber junit
-Note that we will add other dependencies that will be used later
==>Right click on test > java and create the following packages:
-pages (page objects goes here)
-runners (to run and control test cases)
-stepdefinitions(java codes goes here)
-utilities(reusable support classes goes here)
-In Utilities package, create classes: Driver,ConfigReader
-Right click on the projects and Create  configuration.properties file
-Right click on test and create a new directory: resources
-Right click on resources and create a new directory: features     (non java staff will go here)
-right click on features->new->file->firstfeaturefile.feature
-Add cucumber plugin to work with intelliJ IDE
-(Mac)IntelliJ Idea->Preference->Plugins->Marketplace->Type Cucumber for Java->Install->Restart
-(Windows)File->Setting->->Plugins->Marketplace->Type Cucumber for Java->Install->Restart